content:
For compliance reasons, some Government Cloud organizations canâ€™t use a content delivery network (CDN). The Salesforce CDN is turned off by default for all new sites created from Government Cloud orgs that have enabled Enhanced Domains.

Where: This change applies to Lightning Experience and Salesforce Classic in Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer editions.

How: To turn on the CDN, from Setup, enter My Domain, select it, then in the Routing section, select Use Content Delivery Network (CDN) by default when enhanced domains are enabled for Experience Cloud sites.
title: Salesforce Content Delivery Network Changes
